
    Constant::FromGlobal

    A perl module for declaring constants with value from global
    or environment variables

This module builds on the 'constant' pragma, defining constants that
take their values from an evironment variable or a global variable.
See the documentation for more details.

You should be able to install this using your usual method for installing
modules from CPAN. If you don't have one let, have a look at:

    http://www.cpan.org/modules/INSTALL.html

The module was written by Yuval Kogman, but is now maintained by
Neil Bowers
neilb@cpan.org
